Reference-contexts: Miniswitch cards are PC-based. Several application cards, including multimedia cards, cell generator cards, network analyzer cards and others, that can be connected to the NIC were implemented. In the following we describe the various components of the network. The ring is built using buffer insertion ring (BIR) architecture <ref> [3, 7] </ref> with cell removal by the destination [6]. Such a ring does not use tokens for its transmission scheduling and allows spatial reuse, i.e., it can support simultaneous transmissions over different segments of the network. <p> As a result, the total ring throughput can be significantly higher than the capacity of a single link (which limits other ring architectures) . The principle of the BIR operation is as follows <ref> [3] </ref>. On the receiving side of each link, there is an insertion buffer (IB), which can store one ATM cell. A node may start a cell transmission at any time if its IB is empty and if there is no ring traffic on its incoming link.
