Reference-contexts: The interconnection device (miniswitch) is a PC card that can connect three rings as well as its local host. It is built using a shared bus architecture with output buffering <ref> [8] </ref>. This architecture was selected due to its simplicity and because interconnecting a larger number of rings is not anticipated. In addition, the miniswitch supports multicast transmission which is important for multimedia conferencing applications.
